Males have relatively longer antenna than females, antennomeres 10 and 11 modified; trochanters and mesofemur with spines or projections on ventral margins; sternite 2 (IV) with three pairs of basolateral foveae; aedeagus (
Fig. 42H, I
) asymmetric, stout, with long basoventral projection, median lobe with large basal capsule, dorsal lobe embracing median lobe and with elongate sclerite, parameres reduced to single membranous structure. Female with two pairs of basolateral foveae on sternite 2 (IV); genitalia (
Fig. 42J
) weakly sclerotized.
